  "The alignment is a random coincidence": "",
  "The 18.6-year lunar nodal cycle (major standstill) causes the Moon's rising point to reach extreme positions. Detecting that ancient builders tracked this slow cycle demonstrates remarkably patient, multi-generational astronomical observation.": "",
  "Egyptian farmers relied on the heliacal rising of Sirius. If climate change shifted the Nile's flooding pattern but Sirius's rising stayed the same, what problem would arise?": "",
  "The calendar would automatically adjust itself": "",
  "Sirius would also change its position to match the new flood timing": "",
  "No problem — calendars are not connected to agriculture": "",
  "The calendar would no longer accurately predict the floods, since the astronomical event and the agricultural event became decoupled": "",
  "This illustrates a key vulnerability of astronomically-based agricultural calendars. If the environmental event (flooding) shifts due to climate change while the astronomical marker (Sirius rising) stays constant, the calendar loses its practical value.": "",
  "A student asks: 'The Maya predicted eclipses without telescopes. How is that possible?' What is the best explanation?": "",
  "They observed eclipse patterns over centuries and noticed mathematical cycles (like the Saros cycle) that repeat predictably": "",
  "They had telescopes but hid them": "",
  "They received the information from space travelers": "",
