  "Equinox alignments are found in structures worldwide (e.g., Angkor Wat, the Parthenon, Mnajdra temples). These deliberate alignments served practical (marking planting seasons) and ceremonial (ritual celebrations) purposes.": "",
  "Chinese records from 1054 CE describe a 'guest star' visible in daylight for 23 days. Modern astronomers linked this record to the Crab Nebula. What does this demonstrate?": "",
